What are Channels and Kernels (according to EVA)?
    
In AI complex large things are built from large number of tiny distinguishable features. Like the alphabets forming meaningful words these distinguishable features can form complex objects. In the assignment 1A the vertical or horizontal edges are features.  A channel is a collection of features of the same type.
A kernel or extractor is a method used for extracting a feature from a complex object.
In assignment 1A, the code for the Horizontal Edge Detector is the kernel.

Why should we only (well mostly) use 3x3 Kernels?

With 3X3 kernel, the cells are clearly addressable like left, right or up down.  
Convolving with a 3x3 kernel repeatedly, we can cover an image of any size.

How many times do we need to perform 3x3 convolution operation to reach 1x1 from 199x199 (show calculations)

100 operations.

